# IntelliSFX Environment Configuration Example
# Copy this file to .env.local and replace the placeholder values with your actual Supabase credentials

# Supabase Configuration
# Get these values from your Supabase project dashboard at https://supabase.com/dashboard

# Your Supabase project URL - found in Settings > API
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=your_supabase_project_url_here

# Your Supabase anon/public key - found in Settings > API
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_supabase_anon_key_here

# Your Supabase service role key - found in Settings > API
# This is needed for server-side operations in the migrated API routes
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your_supabase_service_role_key_here

# Setup Instructions:
# 1. Create a new Supabase project at https://supabase.com
# 2. Copy this file to .env.local in the project root
# 3. Replace the placeholder values above with your actual Supabase credentials
# 4. Create the following storage buckets in your Supabase dashboard (Storage > Buckets):
#    - videos (for uploaded video files)
#    - audio (for generated audio files)
#    - thumbnails (for video thumbnails)
# 5. Set appropriate bucket policies for public access as needed
# 6. Run 'npm run dev' to start the development server

# Note: Never commit .env.local to version control - it contains sensitive credentials
